Implement the session ID remap flow using `store.renameSession()` to atomically swap the store key when the server assigns a different session ID in the `done` event. Remove the `isRemappingRef` pattern.

## Implementation

### Step 1: Update the done event handler in StreamManager

In `StreamManager.dispatchEvent` (or the refactored event handler), update the `done` case to use `renameSession`:

```typescript
case 'done': {
  const doneData = data as DoneEvent;
  if (doneData.sessionId && doneData.sessionId !== sessionId) {
    const store = useSessionChatStore.getState();

    // Flush current streaming state to messages before remap
    const session = store.getSession(sessionId);
    if (session.assistantCreated && session.currentParts.length > 0) {
      const parts = session.currentParts.map((p) => ({ ...p }));
      const derived = deriveFromParts(parts);
      store.updateSession(sessionId, {
        messages: session.messages.map((m) =>
          m._streaming && m.role === 'assistant'
            ? {
                ...m,
                content: derived.content,
                toolCalls: derived.toolCalls.length > 0 ? derived.toolCalls : [],
                parts,
              }
            : m
        ),
        currentParts: [],
        assistantCreated: false,
      });
    }

    // Atomic key swap BEFORE URL update
    store.renameSession(sessionId, doneData.sessionId);

    // Move AbortController entry in StreamManager
    const controller = this.activeStreams.get(sessionId);
    if (controller) {
      this.activeStreams.set(doneData.sessionId, controller);
      this.activeStreams.delete(sessionId);
    }

    // Move timers entry
    const timers = this.timers.get(sessionId);
    if (timers) {
      this.timers.set(doneData.sessionId, timers);
      this.timers.delete(sessionId);
    }

    // Fire URL update -- React re-renders, reads from new key, data already there
    options.onSessionIdChange?.(doneData.sessionId);
  }

  // ... rest of done handling (messageIds remap, streaming metrics, etc.)
}
```

### Step 2: Remove isRemappingRef

In `use-chat-session.ts`, remove:
```typescript
const isRemappingRef = useRef(false);
```

Also remove the `isRemappingRef` check in the session-change reset effect:
```typescript
// REMOVE:
useEffect(() => {
  if (isRemappingRef.current) {
    isRemappingRef.current = false;
    historySeededRef.current = true;
    return;
  }
  historySeededRef.current = false;
  if (statusRef.current !== 'streaming') {
    setMessages([]);
  }
}, [sessionId, selectedCwd]);
```

Replace with a store-based approach:
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (!sessionId) return;
  const store = useSessionChatStore.getState();
  const session = store.getSession(sessionId);

  // If the session is remapping, mark historySeeded for incremental dedup
  if (session.isRemapping) {
    store.updateSession(sessionId, { isRemapping: false, historySeeded: true });
    return;
  }

  // Reset history seed flag for fresh session loads
  store.updateSession(sessionId, { historySeeded: false });
}, [sessionId, selectedCwd]);
```

### Step 3: Set isRemapping in store before remap

In the done event handler, before calling `renameSession`:
```typescript
// Set isRemapping on the NEW session ID so the effect knows it's a remap
store.renameSession(sessionId, doneData.sessionId);
store.updateSession(doneData.sessionId, { isRemapping: true });
```

### Step 4: Remove isRemappingRef from StreamEventDeps

Remove `isRemappingRef` from the `StreamEventDeps` / `StreamDispatchContext` interface.

